WASHINGTON (AP) -- Although the IRS is making some progress, a   new audit says chronic computer system weaknesses continue to place  sensitive taxpayer data at risk of theft, fraud and even misuse by  hackers.
   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- The stockpile of public information is as potentially frightening as it is extensive: professors display test results by social security numbers, the long and revealing trail of E-Z pass tags, and prisoners -- at least in other states -- uncover personal information of innocent citizens.
